# Insertion Sort - Complete Interview Revision Notes

# One-Line Definition

```text
Pick one element at a time and insert it into its correct position
in the already sorted part of the array.
```

# Core Idea

Selection Sort:

```text
Find minimum and place it.
```

Bubble Sort:

```text
Push maximum to the end.
```

Insertion Sort:

```text
Take current element and insert it into the sorted portion.


# Algorithm

## Steps

1. Assume first element is sorted.
2. Pick next element (key).
3. Compare with previous elements.
4. Shift larger elements right.
5. Insert key at correct position.
6. Repeat until end.

# Java Implementation

```java
import java.util.Arrays;

public class InsertionSort {

    public static void insertionSort(int[] arr) {

        int n = arr.length;

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {

            int key = arr[i];

            int j = i - 1;

            while (j >= 0 && arr[j] > key) {

                arr[j + 1] = arr[j];

                j--;
            }

            arr[j + 1] = key;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] arr = {5, 3, 4, 1, 2};

        insertionSort(arr);

        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr));
    }
}
```
